  "prompt": "Are there some people who just looks better without makeup than with makeup?",
  "response": "Yes, some people may look better without makeup than with it, and this can be subjective. Factors that contribute to this perception include natural skin texture, facial features, and personal style. Additionally, some individuals may prefer a more natural look or feel more confident without makeup. Personal preferences and societal beauty standards also play a significant role in how makeup is perceived. Ultimately, beauty is subjective, and what looks good varies from person to person.",
